{"title_page": "Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 21st Baron Clinton", "text_new": "'''Charles John Robert Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 21st Baron Clinton''' {{postnominals|country=GBR|GCVO|PC}} (18 January 1863 &ndash; 5 July 1957) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Peerage|peer]].\n\nTrefusis was the eldest son of the [[Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 20th Baron Clinton|20th Baron Clinton]] and his wife, Harriet. Educated at [[Oxford University|Oxford]] he played polo with the University team and won the [[The Varsity Polo Match|Varsity Match]] against Cambridge in 1883.<ref>{{cite news|title=Polo. Oxford v. Cambridge|newspaper=The Times|date=18 June 1883}}</ref>  On 1 June 1886, he married Lady Jane McDonnell (15 June 1863 &ndash; 27 August 1953) (a daughter of the [[Mark McDonnell, 5th Earl of Antrim|5th Earl of Antrim]]) and they had two daughters:\n\n*Hon. Harriet (14 November 1887 &ndash; 15 March 1958), married Maj. Henry Nevile Fane (1883 &ndash; 2 August 1947). They had seven children.\n*[[Fenella Bowes-Lyon|Hon. Fenella]] (19 August 1889 &ndash; 19 July 1966), married [[John Herbert Bowes-Lyon|Hon. John Bowes-Lyon]]. They had five children.\n\nFrom 1898 until he succeeded to his father's title in 1904, Trefusis was [[Convener]] of [[Kincardineshire]] County Council. In 1911, Lord Clinton was admitted to the [[Duchy of Cornwall]] Council and was appointed the duchy's Keeper of the Privy Seal in 1913 and [[Lord Warden of the Stannaries]] in 1921. From 1918\u201319, he was Joint [[Parliamentary Secretary to the Board of Agriculture and Fisheries]], Chairman of the [[Forestry Commission]] from 1927\u201329, and a director of the [[Southern Railway (Great Britain)|Southern Railway]].<ref name=\"steamindex\">{{cite web\n  | last = Jones\n  | first = Kevin P\n  | authorlink =\n  | title = Biographies of chairmen, managers & other senior railway officers\n  | work = SteamIndex\n  | publisher =\n  | date =\n  | url = http://www.steamindex.com/people/managers.htm\n  | accessdate = 2009-03-16}}</ref>  Lord Clinton had also been admitted to the [[Privy Council of the United Kingdom|Privy Council]] in 1927 and on his retirement in 1933, he was appointed a [[Royal Victorian Order|GCVO]].\n\nUpon Lord Clinton's death in 1957, his title became [[abeyance|abeyant]] between his two daughters until it was called out of abeyance for his great-grandson (by Harriet), [[Gerard Fane-Trefusis, 22nd Baron Clinton|Gerard]] in 1965.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://www.burkes-peerage.net/ Burke's Peerage & Gentry]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-court}}\n{{s-bef| before = [[William Edgcumbe, 4th Earl of Mount Edgcumbe|The Earl of Mount Edgcumbe]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Duchy of Cornwall|Keeper of the Privy Seal of the Duchy of Cornwall]]\n       | years  = 1913 &ndash; 1933 }}\n{{s-aft| rows   = 2 | after  = [[William Pleydell-Bouverie, 7th Earl of Radnor|The Earl of Radnor]] }}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Alexander Bruce, 6th Lord Balfour of Burleigh|The Lord Balfour of Burleigh]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Lord Warden of the Stannaries]]\n       | years  = 1921 &ndash; 1933 }}\n\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Charles Spencer-Churchill, 9th Duke of Marlborough|The Duke of Marlborough]] <br/> [[George Goschen, 2nd Viscount Goschen|The Viscount Goschen]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Parliamentary Secretary to the Board of Agriculture and Fisheries|Joint Parliamentary Secretary<br>to the Board of Agriculture and Fisheries]]\n       | with   = [[Richard Winfrey|Sir Richard Winfrey]]\n       | years  = 1918 &ndash; 1919 }}\n{{s-aft| after  = [[Arthur Griffith-Boscawen|Sir Arthur Griffith-Boscawen]] }}\n\n{{s-reg|en}}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 20th Baron Clinton|Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Baron Clinton]]\n       | years  = 1904 &ndash; 1957 }}\n{{s-vac| abeyance | next = [[Gerald Fane-Trefusis, 22nd Baron Clinton|Gerald Fane-Trefusis]] }}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clinton, Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 21st Baron}}\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Knights Grand Cross of the Royal Victorian Order]]\n[[Category:1863 births]]\n[[Category:1957 deaths]]\n[[Category:Barons Clinton]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) hereditary peers]]\n", "text_old": "'''Charles John Robert Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 21st Baron Clinton''' {{postnominals|country=GBR|GCVO|PC}} (18 January 1863 &ndash; 5 July 1957) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Peerage|peer]].\n\nTrefusis was the eldest son of the [[Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 20th Baron Clinton|20th Baron Clinton]] and his wife, Harriet. Educated at [[Oxford University|Oxford]] he played polo with the University team and won the [[The Varsity Polo Match|Varsity Match]] against Cambridge in 1883.<ref>{{cite news|title=Polo. Oxford v. Cambridge|newspaper=The Times|date=18 June 1883}}</ref>  On 1 June 1886, he married Lady Jane McDonnell (15 June 1863 &ndash; 27 August 1953) (a daughter of the [[Mark McDonnell, 5th Earl of Antrim|5th Earl of Antrim]]) and they had two daughters:\n\n*Hon. Harriet (14 November 1887 &ndash; 15 March 1958), married Maj. Henry Nevile Fane (1883 &ndash; 2 August 1947). They had seven children.\n*[[Fenella Bowes-Lyon|Hon. Fenella]] (19 August 1889 &ndash; 19 July 1966), married [[John Herbert Bowes-Lyon|Hon. John Bowes-Lyon]]. They had five children.\n\nFrom 1898 until he succeeded to his father's title in 1904, Trefusis was [[Convener]] of [[Kincardineshire]] County Council. In 1911, Lord Clinton was admitted to the [[Duchy of Cornwall]] Council and was appointed the duchy's Keeper of the Privy Seal in 1913 and [[Lord Warden of the Stannaries]] in 1921. From 1918-19, he was Joint [[Parliamentary Secretary to the Board of Agriculture and Fisheries]], Chairman of the [[Forestry Commission]] from 1927\u201329, and a director of the [[Southern Railway (Great Britain)|Southern Railway]].<ref name=\"steamindex\">{{cite web\n  | last = Jones\n  | first = Kevin P\n  | authorlink =\n  | title = Biographies of chairmen, managers & other senior railway officers\n  | work = SteamIndex\n  | publisher =\n  | date =\n  | url = http://www.steamindex.com/people/managers.htm\n  | accessdate = 2009-03-16}}</ref>  Lord Clinton had also been admitted to the [[Privy Council of the United Kingdom|Privy Council]] in 1927 and on his retirement in 1933, he was appointed a [[Royal Victorian Order|GCVO]].\n\nUpon Lord Clinton's death in 1957, his title became [[abeyance|abeyant]] between his two daughters until it was called out of abeyance for his great-grandson (by Harriet), [[Gerard Fane-Trefusis, 22nd Baron Clinton|Gerard]] in 1965.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://www.burkes-peerage.net/ Burke's Peerage & Gentry]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-court}}\n{{s-bef| before = [[William Edgcumbe, 4th Earl of Mount Edgcumbe|The Earl of Mount Edgcumbe]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Duchy of Cornwall|Keeper of the Privy Seal of the Duchy of Cornwall]]\n       | years  = 1913 &ndash; 1933 }}\n{{s-aft| rows   = 2 | after  = [[William Pleydell-Bouverie, 7th Earl of Radnor|The Earl of Radnor]] }}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Alexander Bruce, 6th Lord Balfour of Burleigh|The Lord Balfour of Burleigh]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Lord Warden of the Stannaries]]\n       | years  = 1921 &ndash; 1933 }}\n\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Charles Spencer-Churchill, 9th Duke of Marlborough|The Duke of Marlborough]] <br/> [[George Goschen, 2nd Viscount Goschen|The Viscount Goschen]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Parliamentary Secretary to the Board of Agriculture and Fisheries|Joint Parliamentary Secretary<br>to the Board of Agriculture and Fisheries]]\n       | with   = [[Richard Winfrey|Sir Richard Winfrey]]\n       | years  = 1918 &ndash; 1919 }}\n{{s-aft| after  = [[Arthur Griffith-Boscawen|Sir Arthur Griffith-Boscawen]] }}\n\n{{s-reg|en}}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 20th Baron Clinton|Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis]] }}\n{{s-ttl| title  = [[Baron Clinton]]\n       | years  = 1904 &ndash; 1957 }}\n{{s-vac| abeyance | next = [[Gerald Fane-Trefusis, 22nd Baron Clinton|Gerald Fane-Trefusis]] }}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clinton, Charles Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis, 21st Baron}}\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Knights Grand Cross of the Royal Victorian Order]]\n[[Category:1863 births]]\n[[Category:1957 deaths]]\n[[Category:Barons Clinton]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) hereditary peers]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1918-19 \u2192 1918\u201319", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Hepburn-Stuart-Forbes-Trefusis,_21st_Baron_Clinton"}
